SIMPLE: haze
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Haze
<hw>Haze</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>h⟦oum⟧ss</ets> gray; akin to AS. <ets>hasu</ets>, <ets>heasu</ets>,
gray; or Armor. <ets>a⟦eacute⟧zen</ets>, <ets>⟦eacute⟧zen</ets>, warm
vapor, exhalation, zephyr.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Light vapor or smoke
in the air which more or less impedes vision, with little or no
dampness; a lack of transparency in the air; hence, figuratively,
obscurity; dimness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O'er the sky⟦br⟧
The silvery <qex>haze</qex> of summer drawn.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Above the world's uncertain <qex>haze</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A state of confusion, uncertainty, or vagueness of
thought or perception; <as>as, after the explosion, people were
wandering around in a <ex>haze</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Haze</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Haze
<hw>Haze</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be hazy, or thick with
haze.</def> <rj><au>Ray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Haze</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Haze
<hw>Haze</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Hazed</conjf> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧zd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hazing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <altsp>[Also <asp>hase</asp>.]</altsp>
<ety>[Cf. Sw. <ets>haza</ets> to hamstring, fr. <ets>has</ets> hough,
OD. <ets>h⟦ae⟧ssen</ets> ham.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To harass by
exacting unnecessary, disagreeable, or difficult work.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To harass or annoy by playing abusive or shameful
tricks upon; to humiliate by practical jokes; -- used esp. of college
students, as an initiation rite into a fraternity or other group;
<as>as, the sophomores <ex>hazed</ex> a freshman</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hazel</ent>⟦br⟧
